The present peaceful way of settling disputes does no longer imply the renunciation of force, but co-operation is still seen as the most reasonable way of solving political conflicts. Kulbss' balanced approach to different problems has been received well not only at home, but continues to be appreciated everywhere in the world.

Tallinn has invited experts in the fields of administration, economy, science and culture to the International Economic Forum from 21-25 Sept. 1991 to strengthen this development. The leaders of these sectors as well as representatives of local governments, specialists of different information systems and business circles will discuss the problems of productivity increasing and the deterioration of economic ties - each of the participant countries is experiencing similar problems. The quest for successful examples of managers of other economies will be playing an important part at the Forum. One of the key purposes of the Forum is to develop co-operation possibilities and market relations between Estonia and the seeking countries of the world.

The Forum provides a unique chance to H. J. Kulbss, The Speaker of Parliament of Estonia, to inform persons interested in the quick development of Estonia about the new situation created for the country by it's peaceful transition to independence.
